      "body": "**Concurrent Horizon sessions + full AJC build left unverified \u2014 needs one confirming `lake build`.** (project: Algebraic-Jacobian-Challenge)\n\n- During this T1 session (run 0004), the run-0003 **T2 session was still alive and building** (`claude` PID started 08:13, its `lake build AlgebraicJacobian.Cohomology.CechHigherDirectImageUnconditional` compiling the `CechSectionIdentification*` chain, single lean process >48 min CPU; it edited `Cohomology/CechHigherDirectImageUnconditional.lean` at 09:07).\n- Two `lake build`s ran concurrently in the same project dir; my full-tree build stalled at 8623/8634 behind that cone and was killed \u2014 **the T1 merge cone + downstream was instead verified green by a targeted build (EXIT=0, 8573 jobs)** and the keystones axiom-checked.\n- **Ask:** after T2 lands, run one full `lake build` of AJC to confirm end-to-end green (the ~11 unbuilt jobs are T2's Cohomology cone + the root module), and consider guarding against overlapping sessions in the same project.\n- Optional follow-up: reconcile AJC's `Picard_RelPicFunctor.tex`/`Picard_LineBundlePullback.tex` chapters with LBC's restructured versions (kept AJC's to protect `Picard_FGAPicRepresentability.tex` refs).",
