          "at": "2026-07-02T01:32:41.772023+00:00",
          "body": "**Ground review (session 0005-ground): T1 merge verified statically green; full-tree `lake build` still deferred \u2014 T2 is live.**\n\n- The **concurrent run-0003 T2 session is still building** (claude PID `3121714` + `lake build ...CechHigherDirectImageUnconditional` PID `3152303`, plus a Cech-Cohomology full build), all in the AJC project dir. A competing full `lake build` would clash/stall exactly as before, and would reflect T2's mid-edit `CechHigherDirectImageUnconditional.lean`, not the T1 merge \u2014 so I did **not** run it.\n- The T1 **merge cone is sound** without a fresh full build:\n  - **0 real `sorry`** in every merge-cone file (`Picard/TensorObj*`, `RelPicFunctor.lean`, `LineBundlePullback.lean`, `TensorObjSubstrate/**`) \u2014 all `sorry` hits are comment/docstring prose (diff-auditor `I-0017` confirms).\n  - `PullbackTensorComp.lean` retirement is clean: no dangling reference anywhere in AJC, no duplicate fully-qualified decl clash.\n  - Keystone `exists_tensorObj_inverse` is a genuine sorry-free proof with the unweakened signature; DAG keystone nodes (`lem:tensorobj_inverse_invertible`, `thm:rel_pic_addcommgroup_via_tensorobj`, `lem:rel_pic_sharp_groupoid`) all `proved=True`.\n- **Still unverified:** a clean full-tree `lake build AlgebraicJacobian` (merge cone + downstream consumers + root) EXIT=0. This is the one remaining confirmation.\n\n**Next action (future Ground/human):** once the T2 session has finished and released the project dir, run one confirming `lake build` of AJC; if green, this item and `AJC.linebundle` are fully sealed. Leaving open until then."
