      "body": "**Cech-Cohomology SubProject: capstone copy was stale vs AJC \u2014 ported the fix; standalone green not confirmable in-session.**\n\nSession `0017-ground` checked the Cech-Cohomology whole-project build:\n\n- **24 of 25 modules replay clean and sorry-free** under v4.31 (the 3 `sorry` string hits are docstring prose, not tactics).\n- The capstone `AlgebraicJacobian/Cohomology/CechToHigherDirectImage.lean` (hosts `cech_computes_higherDirectImage`, the `CECH.main` deliverable) had **never had its olean cached** \u2014 every prior full build was killed before reaching it. It carries `maxHeartbeats 4000000` and compiles single-threaded for **>1.5 h**.\n- That SubProject copy was also **stale vs the merged AJC copy** (which has a fresh olean \u21d2 verified): they differed only in the proof of `mapAlternatingCofaceMapComplexIso` (SubProject had the pre-v4.31 form) and a missing `set_option backward.isDefEq.respectTransparency false in`.\n\n**Action taken:** ported the AJC-verified copy wholesale into the SubProject (imports identical, only those 2 hunks differed). The heavy `cech_computes_higherDirectImage` theorem was already identical in both copies and compiles in AJC, so the port is low-risk.\n\n**Still open:** a confirming `lake build` of the ported module was **still compiling at session end** (the 4M-heartbeat cost + contention from a live concurrent Horizon session, PID 3121714). Green for the standalone SubProject is therefore **not confirmed this session** \u2014 needs one long uncontended build to finish. The deliverable itself is verified in AJC (`AJC.cech [done]` stands). See memory `cech-subproject-capstone-stale-vs-ajc` and inbox `I-0016`.",
